AWKA – Anambra-North Women Empowerment Movement (AWEM) through it’s Chairperson has issued stern admonitions to EFCC for it’s reckless and unprofessional behavior towards handling the case of the former Governor Of Anambra State, Chief Willie Obiano. The Chairperson of A.W.E.M, in the person of Chief Mrs Uju Ifunanya Edochie , strongly condemns the vile trending online video clip of Chief Willie Obiano while in EFCC custody. Edochie who issued a statement yesterday in Aguleri, said It was quite obvious that the particular video was taken without Chief Willie Obiano’s knowledge nor consent and as such, noted that the premeditated brouhaha by the EFCC seemed to veer into a caricature and witch-hunting which said is a mockery of Nigeria’s judicial due process. The AWEM chairperson explained that former Governor, Willie Obiano, was one of the leading performing Governors in Nigeria as he had profound achievements in agriculture, health, education, infrastructure, commerce and trade, security, employment rate, civil service as well as state economy. She said under the administration of Willie Obiano, Anambra State experienced a new dawn at sunset. Anambra ranked lowest in poverty index, unemployment rate dropped drastically, three jumbo rice mills were established in different parts of the state, 17 iconic bridges and flyovers were constructed with numerous standard roads throughout the state, functional street and traffic lights were mounted on all roads, built the first Anambra Airport and so on. She however maintained that Ndi Anambra frowns sternly at the disgraceful and unruly act displayed by the EFCC, stressing that appropriate and humane trial tactics should be exercised by EFCC . Chief Uju Ifunanya Edochie also stated that EFCC facility is not safe if they could humiliate an Ex-governor, made video of him in their supposed protective custody , sent to social media for the public to mock. She said the group threatens to protest at EFCC Abuja office stack naked if EFCC doesn’t release urgently ex-governor Obiano.